<HEADLINE>
11 more school students reported falling unconscious in
Bangladesh
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 17 (Xinhua)
</P>
<P>
Eleven more school students of two high schools in Bangladesh's
southwestern Satkhira and central Manikganj districts fell
unconscious Tuesday morning, the private news agency UNB
reported.
</P>
<P>
The two incidents have added the total number of students falling
unconscious in Bangladesh to almost 150 in six similar incidents
since July 14.
</P>
<P>
In Satkhira district, 190 km southwest of the capital Dhaka, nine
students of Moutala High School fell unconscious with convulsion
in the classrooms Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Headmaster Tobarak Hossain said the students suddenly lost their
senses. They were rushed to a local hospital.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, three students of Gonapara Model High School in
Manikganj district, 45 km northwest of Dhaka, fainted with
similar syndrome in their classroom in the morning. They were
admitted to Dhaka Medical Hospital.
</P>
<P>
According to earlier reports of local media on Tuesday, 20 high
school students in western Magura district fainted with
convulsion almost simultaneously in the classroom at 11 a.m.
local time. Also in the morning, 11 girl students in southern
Bagerhat district fell unconscious in their classrooms.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, some 35 students lost senses in the classrooms of a
high school at Savar, 25 km west of Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on July 14, at least 70 students of a high school in
eastern Narsingdi district fell unconscious in their classrooms
with similar syndrome.
</P>
<P>
At present, many of the affected students are still undergoing
treatment in hospitals. Physicians could not ascertain the cause
of the disease. Many said that it might be mass hysteria.
</P>
<P>
Panic spread in these areas following the incidents.
</P>
